post_text:
Central Cass School is excited to announce that we will be able to provide a free breakfast and lunch meal to every Central Cass student, both in-person and virtual students, at no cost due to an extension of the United States Department of Agriculture (USDA) emergency feeding programs as the country continues to recover from the COVID-19 pandemic. The free meals are temporary and will be provided through December 2020 or until available federal funding is exhausted.

Additional items served, such as second servings and a la carte items are not included with the free meal program and these items will be charged to the individual student account.

Current funds in a student account will remain for when charges to meals resume. Families are still encouraged to complete the Free and Reduced Meal Program applications as the free meals are temporary. In addition, there are also other household and school district benefits to qualifying for the Free and Reduced Meal Program.

post_text:
PowerSchool Parent and Student Portal will be reopened on Monday, August 17th at 4:00 pm for grades 5-12. Please login to view homeroom teachers and schedules. Please note: Building access and locker assignments will not be available until Student Orientation Meetings on Monday, August 31st, and Tuesday, September 1st for all Central Cass Students.

See our POWER SCHOOL WEBSITE TAB on the Central Cass Website for tutorials on downloading the PowerSchool app and other details if you need help with your account.

Account Help
Contact Penny Saewert (Penny.Saewert@k12.nd.us) to request your PowerSchool login credentials. Please allow 2-3 business days for a response as our office is not fully staffed until August, 24th.

High School Schedule Changes

High School students will be able to make schedule changes beginning Tuesday, August 18th by scheduling a face-to-face or virtual meeting with Mrs. Ziegelmann. Drop in schedule changes will not be available for the 2020-2021 school year.

Here is the link for students to make appointments for schedule changes: https://calendly.com/mrs-ziegelmann

June 9, 2020 Election Information

For this election all voting will be mail-in ONLY. Cass County residents who were listed in the Central Voter File will receive a letter in the mail from the Secretary of State between April 20 and April 30 with information regarding the June election AND an application for the mail in ballot. You MUST return this self-addressed postage paid application to receive a ballot for voting.

If you do not receive an application for voting in the mail you can go online to www.vote.nd.gov and fill out, print, sign and mail your application to your county auditor. You can also call the Cass County Auditor directly 701-241-5600 and they can mail an application to you.

shared_text:
Central Cass School District #17
March 3 at 4:23 PM ¬∑

We are happy to announce we have enough students registered, with paid deposits, to fill one Regular Education Pre-Kindergarten classroom for the 2020-2021 school year! Registration will remain open in hopes of filling a second classroom, which we are already partway there.

If you are interested in being put on the waiting list or learning more about our Pre-Kindergarten program, please see our website at https://www.central-cass.k12.nd.us/Page/534

Please note the second section will only happen if there is enough interest. To allow for hiring high-quality staff, we will make final decisions on a second section prior to May 1st.
Register your child today or share this amazing opportunity with any family looking for Pre-Kindergarten instruction for the 2020-2021 school year! Thank you!

North Dakota is joining Minnesota tonight with a "Stadium Lights Night" to honor students, staff, parents, and community members during this time of distance learning and closed schools due to the COVID-19 crises. Lights will be turned on tonight, April 3rd at 7:00 PM and be shut off at 10:00 PM.

This is meant to be a symbol of HOPE and assurance that students are in our hearts and on our minds.

You can drive by and check it out while practicing social distancing!

Are you interested in running for Central Cass School Board?

The deadline for filing to have a candidate‚Äôs name printed on the ballot for the Central Cass School District School Board Election is April 6, 2020, by 4:00 p.m. The following school board positions are up for election:

Southeast Area #4 All of Everest Township and portions of Casselton, Harmony, Raymond, Durbin, Maple River, Addison, and Leonard Townships‚Äì 3-year term.

At-Large ‚Äì 3-year term.

A candidate for a school district office must turn in a completed statement of candidacy and a completed Statement of Interest to Pamela Utt, Business Manager by the above deadline and time. All forms are available from the office of the Business Manager at 802 5th St N, Casselton ND 58012. To make arrangements to receive or return completed forms by email, mail, or pick up in front of the school, please contact Pam Utt at pam.utt@k12.nd.us or at 701-346-2007. Thank you!

FYI: Please see the statement from the North Dakota High School Activities Association on the attached link. https://ndhsaa.com/news/1685/statement-on-the-suspension-of-all-remaining-2020-ndhsaa-winter-postseason-tournaments-fine-arts-contests-spring-sports-activities

Note from Mr. Lemar: Please keep in mind that the statement says "suspended indefinitely" and not canceled like the NCAA. I would encourage student-athletes and fine arts participants to continue to practice their skill outside of organized practices so it is a very short period of time to get back to participation when we are allowed. The School Leadership Team will be in constant communication as we do our best to try and answer questions and communicate a plan for what lies ahead. Please be patient and we will do our best to keep you informed as information gets passed onto us and decisions are made. For now, all practices and events sanctioned by the NDHSAA are on hold. Thank you.

post_text:
We are happy to announce we have enough students registered, with paid deposits, to fill one Regular Education Pre-Kindergarten classroom for the 2020-2021 school year! Registration will remain open in hopes of filling a second classroom, which we are already partway there.

If you are interested in being put on the waiting list or learning more about our Pre-Kindergarten program, please see our website at https://www.central-cass.k12.nd.us/Page/534

Please note the second section will only happen if there is enough interest. To allow for hiring high-quality staff, we will make final decisions on a second section prior to May 1st.
Register your child today or share this amazing opportunity with any family looking for Pre-Kindergarten instruction for the 2020-2021 school year! Thank you!

post_text: Spring is here, are you thinking about your garden? Meadowlark Seeds can help! Meadowlark Seeds is a student-run business within the Marketing Department at Central Cass. They sell a variety of fruit, vegetable, and flower seeds. Proceeds from each sale benefit our local DECA chapter. DECA is a high school organization designed to promote education in the fields of marketing, finance, hospitality, and management giving the students an opportunity to compete at the state and international levels. Please call 1-800-493-SEED(7333) to request a catalog or visit www.central-cass.k12.nd.us/meadowlarkseeds to view the catalog online. Your purchase is greatly appreciated.

post_text: At the beginning of the Kids Heart Challenge, the students set a goal to raise $10,000. As an incentive to beat the goal, Physical Education Teachers Ms. Vaudrin and Mr. Nelson offered to get pies thrown at them. It was a record-breaking year as more students than ever before participated and a grand total of $15,671 was raised for the American Heart Association. The top fundraisers got their chance today to pie the teachers in the face, during Morning Assembly. Thank you to everyone who helped raise money for this great cause!

UPSTART (Free At-Home Kindergarten Readiness Program) Info: Registration is now open for 500+ families! State Superintendent Kirsten Baesler was recently featured in a video explaining why UPSTART is a wonderful solution for all families across North Dakota. Check it out here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AVQfDPTuTYE&feature=youtu.be

This is UPSTART‚Äôs second year in North Dakota! Eligible families will have a child attending kindergarten in the fall of 2021. Each family will receive a free Dell laptop as a part of the program. Internet service is provided for families who need it.

Waterford UPSTART is not an online preschool. It is a program that engages & prepares children and supports families for Kindergarten and academic success in school.

FREE to families, this program is funded through a grant from the U.S. Department of Education called Education, Research, and Innovation (EIR).

Please see the attached flyer for registration and contact information.

Premier Night! What great talent The Film Dudes were able to showcase with our 3rd grade classes creating 4 movie trailers while K-2, 4-5 showed their Mannequin Challenge skills off.

This school year we were blessed to host The Film Dudes, Eric and Matt, for two weeks. They spent their time teaching acting, filmmaking, and social media basics to each grade level (K-5) for a week this fall. Their second week was focused on our core group with 3rd grade going a little more in depth to create the movie trailers.

We will be sharing Trailers, Mannequin Challenges, and a Behind the Scenes film once we have all of them ready to go.

Thanks to everyone who was able to join us tonight for our Premier Night!

Thanks to the ND Council of Arts to allow these great talents to be brought into our school.
